# product-card-9x16.note

A 6-second vertical product card: name + tagline + accent shape, in the brand palette.
Vertical (9:16) so it fits social shorts. Copy this brief, change the product name +
colors, then hit Generate.

---

**Target duration:** 6 s
**Aspect:** 9:16
**Camera hint:** subtle slow zoom-in on the title

**Scene prompt (paste into Generate panel)**:

> Centered product card. Big sans-serif product name slides up from y+80px into y=0
> over the first 20 frames. A one-line tagline fades in 10 frames later. A solid
> color accent bar (40px tall, half-width) draws in from the left under the tagline
> at frame 35. Hold from frame 60 to frame 150. Background is a smooth radial
> gradient from accent color (centered, faded) to near-black at the edges.

**Replace these tokens before generating**:

| Token | Example |
|---|---|
| Product name | `Aurora Pen` |
| Tagline | `One stroke, sixty four colors.` |
| Accent color | `#7DD3FC` |

**References**:

- product card style, not a hero shot
- accent color used only for the slim bar (no full backgrounds in accent)
- tagline font ~3.5x smaller than the product name

**Why this clip works as a template**

- Three element types only (title / tagline / accent) keeps the agent's output
  short and easy to read.
- 6 s is long enough to register but short enough that you'll regenerate
  freely while iterating on the brief.
